<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-64-0637 </DOCNO><TEXT>Knowledge-based expert systems may provide the mine operator with a powerfultool to improve the maintainability of mining machines. Specifically,they could allow for a problem to be diagnosed more accurately and quicklythan is presently possible, at least in some situations. Furthermore,the system could provide a similar benefit in recommending a repair action.The purpose of the project described in this paper was to investigatethe nature and cost of a development effort which would result in sucha system for one mining machine.</TEXT></DOC>